        <h2>Rebirth as Praxis Initiative</h2>
        <p>At our 2024 strategic retreat, the board made a unanimous decision: evolve from a single-issue watchdog into a comprehensive justice organization. We chose the name Praxis Initiative because "praxis" means turning theory into action—the essence of credible messenger advocacy. This rebrand wasn't about abandoning our roots; it was about applying our proven model to the entire criminal legal system while maintaining our oversight work.</p>
        <p>Today, Praxis Initiative operates five programs. We continue monitoring the new Ombudsman's Office through our <strong>Independent Prison Oversight</strong> program, ensuring it fulfills its mandate. Our <strong>Criminal Legal System Reform</strong> and <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> programs tackle pre-trial detention, sentencing, and overdose crisis response. <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training</strong> and <strong>ARTS in Prison & Think Motion</strong> develop the next generation of directly impacted leaders. Our staff has grown from 5 volunteers to 15 paid employees, 100% of whom have lived experience.</p>
