        <h2>Directly Impacted Leadership: Our Non-Negotiable</h2>
        <p>Praxis Initiative is one of the few Arizona nonprofits where lived experience isn't just represented—it's required. Every programmatic decision is made by people who have been incarcerated, deported, or directly impacted by the system. Our Executive Director spent 15 years in ADCRR custody. Our Policy Directors navigated the system as women and youth. This isn't tokenism; it's expertise.</p>
        <p>This structure gives us unmatched credibility. When we testify about prison conditions, we reference specific yards and units. When we draft legislation, we anticipate unintended consequences because we've lived them. When we train returning citizens to advocate, we teach not just the "how" but the "why"—the emotional resilience required to tell your story in a room of skeptical lawmakers. Our leadership model transforms personal trauma into political power.</p>
        <p>Our commitment extends to governance. Our board is majority directly impacted, with mandatory seats for currently incarcerated individuals (voting by proxy). We pay all returning citizen interns and prioritize hiring from communities most affected by Arizona's carceral policies. In 2024, the majority of our budget went directly to formerly incarcerated Arizonans as salary, stipends, or artist fees.</p>
